choices.text:
There are three killers in a room. Someone enters the room and kills one of them. Nobody leaves the room. How many killers are left in the room?
The number of killers remaining in the room would depend on how they were initially arranged when someone entered (possibly by chance). If all three initial positions remain empty, then there will still be one kiler standing. However, if two or more of them have been killed and one is left alive, that person could potentially reenter to replace their dead body. So in this case, we would count only the one living killer as being "left".
